OverHistory.NewCommentry: Megan Schutt to Smriti Mandhana Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Megan Schutt bowling to Smriti Mandhana, good length ball, pitching wide outside off stump, Smriti Mandhana plays an aggressive cut shot WICKET Smriti Mandhana c Beth Mooney b Megan Schutt (India (Women) 9 Runs for 1 wickets) towards Wicket Keeper
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
WICKET! Megan Schutt bowling to Smriti Mandhana, good length ball, pitching wide outside off stump, Smriti attempts a cut shot, seems to have bailed out a fraction too late, and the ball appears to have grazed the edge. The umpires converge to discuss whether the ball carried to Alyssa Mooney, who is confidently claiming the catch. Mandhana, is already halfway back to the pavilion. Unfortunately for India, the replay confirms their worst fears. The edge is clear, and the ball has carried perfectly to Mooney.

Smriti Mandhana c Beth Mooney b Megan Schutt (India (Women) 9 Runs for 1 wickets)towards Wicket Keeper

OverHistory.NewCommentry: Annabel Sutherland to Harmanpreet Kaur Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Annabel Sutherland bowling to Harmanpreet Kaur, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Harmanpreet Kaur plays a defensive forward push WICKET Harmanpreet Kaur lbw Annabel Sutherland (India (Women) 62 Runs for 4 wickets)
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
WICKET! Annabel Sutherland bowling to Harmanpreet Kaur, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Harmanpreet Kaur caught in no man's land, minimal footwork as she leans into the shot, trying to work it leg side. Fatal error - bat closes too early, misses completely, and the ball thuds into the pad! Upstairs we go... but technology confirms what we saw: no bat involved, pitching in line, and Hawkeye shows it clipping leg stump. The umpire's call means Kaur has to go! 

 Harmanpreet Kaur lbw Annabel Sutherland (India (Women) 62 Runs for 4 wickets)

OverHistory.NewCommentry: Ashleigh Gardner to Richa Ghosh Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Ashleigh Gardner bowling to Richa Ghosh, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Richa Ghosh plays a slog sweep for 1 run(s) WICKET Deepti Sharma run out Georgia Wareham (India (Women) 92 Runs for 6 wickets) towards Country
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
WICKET! Ashleigh Gardner bowling to Richa Ghosh, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Richa Ghosh wings hard but doesn't get all of it - high towards deep midwicket where Wareham's positioned. The fielder gathers cleanly and unleashes a rocket throw at the bowler's end! Deepti's scrambling, full-length dive, but wait... there's a twist! The bat's tilted up in the air as the bails come off! Upstairs it goes, side-on angles show the cruel truth - no part of that bat is grounded beyond the line when the stumps light up. The dreaded red light appears, and Deepti has to go for just 1! 

 Deepti Sharma run out Georgia Wareham (India (Women) 92 Runs for 6 wickets)towards Country
